parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Wiper Arm Failure and Entanglement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper arms can cause them to become entangled, leading to a loss of visibility during rain or snow, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers become entangled
the wiper arms collide
the wiper arms stick or fall
the wipers stop working
the wipers do not make good contact with the windshield
the wiper motor mounting plate flexes
causing the wiper linkage to hang up on the motor mounting bolts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Missing/Damaged Parts (Sway Bar Retainer and Bolts)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Missing or damaged parts can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Missing parts
damaged parts
loose or detached components
unusual noises or vibrations while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Welding defects can cause parts to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Missing or loose parts
unusual noises or vibrations while driving
difficulty with repairs due to damaged components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle instability and transmission problems can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle shaking or vibrating
transmission shifting improperly
loss of power
difficulty accelerating
screws dislodging from windshield wipers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Vehicle Movement Due to Transmission Shift Lever Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle rolls into traffic, pedestrians, or other obstacles.
symptoms: The vehicle moves unexpectedly
the transmission shift lever can be moved out of park without the key in the ignition or the brakes applied
the vehicle rolls or moves without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the wiper blades can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially during heavy rain or snow, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiper blades go down too far and get stuck below the windshield
the wiper blades do not move or move erratically
the wiper blades make a loud noise or vibrate excessively
the wiper blades leave streaks or residue on the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the RV ladder mounting system can cause the ladder to separate from the RV, leading to potential falls and injuries, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Screws holding the ladder to the RV are coming loose
noise when climbing up or down the ladder
ladder is separating from the RV
tubes holding the ladder to the RV are bent.
